#### B. Power of Ombudsman-

- 1) The Ombudsman shall receive and consider complaints or disputes relating to-
2. (a) delay  in  settlement  of  claims,  beyond  the  time  specified  in  the  regulations,  framed under the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority of India Act, 1999;
3. (b) any partial or total repudiation of claims by the Company ;
4. (c) disputes over premium paid or payable in terms of insurance policy;
5. (d) misrepresentation of policy terms and conditions at any time in the policy document or policy contract;
6. (e) legal construction of insurance policies in so far as the dispute relates to claim;
7. (f) policy servicing related grievances against insurers and their agents and intermediaries;
